OL,3,CSon uncovers his father's wartime
OL,4,Cjourney in WW1
OL,6,FAt the tender age of 91, Roy Bradley
OL,7,Ffrom Crewe, is only just starting to
OL,8,Flearn about his father's time during
OL,9,Fthe WW1.
OL,11,FArthur Bradley was a lieutenant
OL,12,Fserving with the 7th Battalion, the
OL,13,FCheshire Regiment during the First
OL,14,FWorld War, but when he returned home
OL,15,Fhe seldom spoke about it leaving his
OL,16,Fson Roy to enlist the help of the
OL,17,FCheshire Roll of Honour organisation
OL,18,Fto fill in the gaps.
