OL,3,CSon uncovers his father's wartime
OL,4,Cjourney in WW1
OL,6,FHe then went onto serve in Northern
OL,7,FFrance, where he was captured and
OL,8,Fspent over a year as a prisoner of war
OL,9,Fbefore returning home to Crewe to work
OL,10,Fin Civvie Street.
OL,12,FHis son Roy said: "All these things
OL,13,Fare a mystery to me to be honest. I've
OL,14,Fgot a broad appreciation of the First
OL,15,FWorld War, but no detail, so anything
OL,16,FI find is very enlightening to me."
OL,18,FAnd that's where Steve Benson from the
OL,19,FCheshire Roll of Honour has stepped to
OL,20,Fdo some historical digging to find out
OL,21,Fmore about Lt. Arthur Bradley.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/4
